original: Häger, Nils Rudolf August, civilingenjör, Jönköping, f. 28/5/92 i Sthlm av yrkesinsp. Carl Fredrik August H. o. Ebba Elisabeth von Rothstein. G. 28 m. Maja Tingvall. Barn: Clæs f. 36, Anders 39. — Stud:ex. i Jönköp. 13, KTH (E) 13-17. Stud. vatten-kraftanläggn. i Schweiz 23. Prov-rumsing. v. Elektr. Motorfabr. Fenix i Jönköp. 17, besiktn :ing. v. Sthlms elverk 18, offerting. v. ASEA i Västerås 19-21, konsult, ing. i Jönköp. 22-24, start, tills. m. komp. Sivers & Hägers Elektr. Fabr. i Jönköp. 24, deläg. där 24-30, därefter souschef v. Elektr. A-B Sivers & Häger. Led. av Jönköp. tekn. fören. o. S. Vätterbygdens el-män. Hobbies: äldre urverkskonstr. o. antikviteter.
translated: Häger, Nils Rudolf August, engineer, Jönköping, born May 28, 1892 in Stockholm to the occupational inspector Carl Fredrik August H. and Ebba Elisabeth von Rothstein. Married in 1928 to Maja Tingvall. Children: Clæs born in 1936, Anders in 1939. He graduated from Jönköping high school in 1913, and from KTH (E) in 1913-17. Studied hydroelectric power plants in Switzerland in 1923. Worked as a test engineer at Elektr. Motorfabr. Fenix in Jönköping in 1917, inspector at Stockholm's power plant in 1918, offered a position at ASEA in Västerås from 1919-1921, consultant and engineer in Jönköping from 1922-1924. Started a company called Sivers & Hägers Elektr. Fabr. in Jönköping in 1924, co-owner from 1924-1930, then deputy manager at Elektr. A-B Sivers & Häger. He was a member of Jönköpings engineering association and S. Vätterbygdens electrical-men. His hobbies were older clockworks and antiques.
